SLS 26RS-4402 ORIGINAL
2026 Regular Session
SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 175
BY SENATOR BOUDREAUX
HEALTH DEPARTMENT. Requests the Louisiana Department of Health to study increased
patient access to medically necessary breast pumps by increasing Medicaid reimbursement
and coverage rates for breast pumps.
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To urge and request the Louisiana Department of Health to study increased patient access
3 to medically necessary breast pumps by increasing Medicaid reimbursement and
4 coverage rates for breast pumps from eighty dollars to one hundred forty dollars.
5 WHEREAS, breastfeeding is widely recognized by medical professionals and public
6 health organizations for its substantial health benefits to infants and mothers, including
7 improved infant nutrition, strengthened immune protection, and reduced maternal health
8 risks; and
9 WHEREAS, access to quality breast pumps is essential for many mothers,
10 particularly working mothers, mothers of premature infants, and mothers experiencing
11 medical complications that require expressed breast milk; and
12 WHEREAS, the Medicaid program serves a significant number of pregnant and
13 postpartum women in Louisiana, many of whom rely upon Medicaid coverage to obtain
14 medically necessary breastfeeding equipment; and
15 WHEREAS, current Medicaid reimbursement and coverage rates for breast pumps
16 in Louisiana may not adequately reflect current market costs for durable, effective, and
17 medically appropriate breast pumps; and
18 WHEREAS, insufficient reimbursement rates may limit supplier participation, reduce
